be.signalsync.syncstrategy

Class SyncStrategy

  • java.lang.Object
    • be.signalsync.syncstrategy.SyncStrategy
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    CrossCovarianceSyncStrategy, FingerprintSyncStrategy

    public abstract class SyncStrategy
extends java.lang.Object
    Superclass for the synchronization algorithms. This class contains an abstract method to start the synchronization and two static methods for creation of the algorithms.
    Author:
    Ward Van Assche

    • Method Detail

      • createCrossCovariance

        public static CrossCovarianceSyncStrategy createCrossCovariance()
        This method creates a CrossCovarianceSyncStrategy object by using the default parameters. The default parameters are determined by using the configuration file.

      • createDefault

        public static SyncStrategy createDefault()
        Create the default synchronization algorithm object. This method uses the configuration file to determine the prefered algorithm (key: LATENCY_ALGORITHM).
        Returns:

      • createFingerprint

        public static FingerprintSyncStrategy createFingerprint()
        This method creates a FingerPrintSyncStrategy object by using the default parameters. The default parameters are determined by using the configuration file.

      • findLatencies

        public abstract java.util.List<LatencyResult> findLatencies(java.util.List<float[]> sliceSet)
        This method has to be implemented by a any algorithm subclass and should return a List containing the latency object of non-reference slice.
        Parameters:
        sliceSet - A List of sample arrays. Each sample array contains the samples of a stream slice. The first sample array is the reference slice.
        Returns:
        A List of timestamps in seconds where the slices are synchronized.
